<p><a href="#sdfootnote19anc" name="sdfootnote19sym">19</a>In Polish scholarly literature, the unrivaled description of the new middle-class ethos continues to be Małgorzata Jacyno, <em>Kultura indywidualizmu</em> (Warsaw: PWN, 2007).</p>
<p><a href="#sdfootnote20anc" name="sdfootnote20sym">20</a>In writing about the “observer” and the “observed,” I also intend to emphasize activeness; the concept of the audience may evoke associations with passive contemplation.</p>
<p><a href="#sdfootnote21anc" name="sdfootnote21sym">21</a>Max Horkheimer and Theodor W. Adorno, “The Culture Industry: Enlightenment as Mass Deception,” in <em>Dialectic of Enlightenment: Philosophical Fragments</em>, ed. Gunzelin Schmid Noerr, trans. Edmund Jephcott (Stanford: Stanford University Press, 2002), 116.</p>
